The paper deals with designing a lightweight deep neural network for face attribute prediction, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of depthwise separable convolutions and pointwise convolution to construct Slim Modules is a technique commonly used in neural network architecture design (cs.AI). The application of the Slim-Net for mobile and embedded devices suggests a potential interest in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-categories.
